Here is a simplified version of the commit path in runner.py:

```python
def finish_turn(self, turn):
    response = self.agent.final_message()
    changed = self.worktree.changed_files()
    if not response:
        return TurnResult(committed=False)
    if not changed:
        return TurnResult(committed=False)
    self.git.commit(turn, changed)
    return TurnResult(committed=True)
```

Scenario: the agent edited a file, but it wrote to a path in the base repo instead of the worktree. It then sent a normal final message. Type your answer to two things: 1) which line stops the commit, and 2) one small change that would make this failure easy to diagnose next time.
